{{Quote|There's an ancient temple there still. It was serviced for centuries by the Dark Prophets. It's so steeped in the dark side that it formed its own nexus-one so powerful it interferes with all weaponry and technology except for lightsabers.|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]|<ref name="Ascension">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Ascension]]''</ref>}}
The '''Dark Force Temple''' was a [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] temple established on [[Dromund Kaas/Legends|Dromund Kaas]], one of the many colony worlds of the original [[Sith Empire/Legends|Sith Empire]], and the [[Capital/Legends|Capital]] of the [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|Resurgent Sith Empire]]. The structure was so steeped in the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]] that it became a [[Vergence/Legends|dark side nexus]] within a dark side nexus.

==History==
[[File:Dromund_Kaas_temple.jpg|thumb|left|200px|The Dark Force Temple at night.]]
Built on a lone bit of solid ground in one of [[Dromund Kaas/Legends|Dromund Kaas's]] many marshes, guarded by [[Unidentified Sith statues|statues]], the Temple was built long after the downfall of the [[Sith Empire/Legends|Sith Empire]] following the [[Great Hyperspace War/Legends|Great Hyperspace War]]. While its early history has been lost, it was rediscovered by the Sith during the [[Light and Darkness War]] when the Sith and the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] fought in the marsh surrounding the structure.

It wasn't until [[Darth Millennial]], an apostate [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]] who rejected [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane's]] [[Rule of Two/Legends|Rule of Two]], found the site that the Temple would come to be inhabited again. Founding the [[Dark Force]] religion on Dromund Kaas, Millennial and his disciples claimed the Temple as their headquarters, operating out of it for centuries. The clergymen of this Order, known as the [[Prophets of the Dark Side]] were approached by [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]] sometime after the fall of the Republic and the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and eventually were integrated into the Empire as the Secret Order of the Empire.

During the reign of the Galactic Empire, Prophets such as Lord [[Cronal]] created horrific [[Sithspawn/Legends|Sithspawn]] such as [[Gorc]], [[Picaroon C. Boodle|Pic]], and mutated [[Noghri/Legends|Noghri]]. The Temple served as an elementary training ground for many of the [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor's]] dark side servants including [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Nial Declann]], and was the childhood home of Cronal's oft-abused daughter, [[Sariss]]. Following the rift between the [[Supreme Prophet]] [[Kadann]] and Darth Sidious, the Prophets abandoned Dromund Kaas and fled into hiding on [[Bosthirda/Legends|Bosthirda]]. The Temple remained a place of the dark side, however, and it was within its walls that [[Kyle Katarn]] fell to the dark side. [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] [[Mission to Dromund Kaas (New Republic)|fought]] her way past Sithspawned [[Noghri/Legends|Noghri]], [[Dianoga/Legends|dianoga]] and [[Vornskr]]s to redeem her Master, barely escaping the world alive.

The Temple would once again be [[Duel on Dromund Kaas|visited]] by Jedi in [[44 ABY]], this time by [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] and [[Ben Skywalker]], and [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]] [[Vestara Khai]] who were in search of the hiding place of members of the [[Lost Tribe of Sith]] and [[Abeloth]].<ref name="Ascension" />

